[1
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 1998 14:19:37 GMT-3
Source: Radio New Zealand International, Wellington 25 Jun 1998
Via: Jack Woodall <woodall@bioqmed.ufrj.br>

A six-year-old boy has died of dengue fever in Tonga.
Ninety-eight of 300 blood specimens sent to laboratories in Australia, New
Zealand and Fiji have tested positive [Whatever that means. - Mod.CHC
Although the number of people seeking help for dengue symptoms has
declined, the report quoted a Health Ministry official as saying the
cooperation of the public in destroying breeding places for mosquitoes was
still needed.
